Terraform is an open-source infrastructure-as-code (IaC) tool that enables users to define and manage infrastructure resources declaratively. 
It allows infrastructure to be represented as code, providing a consistent and version-controlled approach to provisioning and managing resources across various cloud providers and on-premises environments. 
Terraform uses a domain-specific language (DSL) to describe the desired infrastructure configuration, and it automates the creation, modification, and deletion of resources while maintaining the desired state.


